com.mp3player.vdp

Class RemoteFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mp3player.vdp.RemoteFile

  • public abstract class RemoteFile
extends java.lang.Object
    A file or directory mounted on any Peer.

    Local files can be mounted using one of VDP's mount methods. To access a remote file, use Peer.getRootFiles() or Peer.getFile(String).

    Mounted directories indirectly mount all contained files and folders. The path of indirectly mounted files then starts with the directly mounted directory, see getPath().

    Once mounted, files should not be changed until unmounted. However, the contents of directories are allowed to change.

    Author:
    Philipp Holl

      • getPath

        public abstract java.lang.String getPath()
        Gets the path to this file under which it is mounted.

        Example: The folder C:/music which contains the file song.mp3 was mounted using VDP.mountFile(File). Then the path to song.mp3 will be music/song.mp3.

        Returns:
        the path to this file under which it is mounted
